{
  "texts": [
    "TRIM is one of the techniques used to adversarially train models with a residual subset of a dataset with a minimum error rate.",
    "M. Jagielski and others [59] have designed and experimented with this TRIM algorithm against adversarial poisoning attacks against linear regression algorithm to solve optimization problems.",
    "This approach has reduced the error rate to approximately 6%.",
    "It performs robustly compared to random sample consensus (RANSAC), a data sanitization derivative, whereas TRIM and RONI security techniques failed against the subpopulation attack developed in [47].",
    "Model hardeningAnother innovative technique to mitigate poisoning attacks is model hardening, in which the model is trained until it leads to large class distances where it should not accept outliers."
  ]
}